er setting `pekko.loglevel = \\\"WARNING\\\"`. The system name should be unique, so I’ll use \\\"extensions-impl-java-singleton-accessor.\\\" There's a problem with loading extensions during ActorSystem startup — it attempts to find a companion object but fails. Editing the reflection config to include the test package should help.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing for file updates**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how Forge generates everything externally, which is good. I need to use edit/write for the changes. The first thing should probably be to move the existing file, so I’ll use bash to handle that with the `mv` command. Once that’s done, I can then focus on writing the new content. It's a straightforward process, but I'm making sure to follow each step carefully to avoid any mistakes!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1Pi31uO4UmryLymZFrmdnfUZ|fc_06228303df04361d016a2a9f3936ec81978413f09fd67fcc86", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "mv tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor-typed_2.13/1.6.0/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_actor_typed_2_13/Pekko_actor_typed_2_13Test.scala tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor-typed_2.13/1.6.0/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_actor_typed_2_13/ExtensionsImplTest.scala", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2825, "output": 1131, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37236, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781178143297, "responseId": "resp_06228303df04361d016a2a9f1fc4948197811152de200687cf"}}
